<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A year on from her first ever trip Down Under, rapper Cardi B is still making waves in Australia.</p>

<p>Her X-rated collaboration with Megan Thee Stallion, titled WAP, has reigned atop the ARIA Singles Chart for the past six weeks.</p>

<p>The song's lengthy stint at No. 1 is a record for the female-led hip hop song.</p>

<p>Making waves: Rapper Cardi B's X-rated collaboration with Megan Thee Stallion (pictured together), titled WAP, has reigned atop the ARIA Singles Chart for the past six weeks</p>

<p>The triumph broke the record previously held by Salt-N-Pepa's 1992 classic, Let's Talk About Sex, earlier this month. </p>

<p>The music video has attracted more than 317million streams on Spotify since it was released on August 6.</p>

<p>The figure does not include the more than 225million views on Youtube. </p>

<p>The raunchy song even spent two weeks at number one on America's Billboard Hot 100 - becoming the first female rap collaboration to debut in the spot.</p>

<p>It also received the most first week streams ever, and has been so popular TikTok users have mashed up the clip - altering its sound and the vocals - to share a variety of other versions online. </p>

<p>Sex appeal: The music video - a collaboration between Cardi B and Megan Thee Stallion (pictured) - has attracted more than 317million views on Spotify since it was released on August 6. The figure does not include the more than 225million views on Youtube</p>

<p>WAP has become a viral sensation - partly due to a cameo from Kylie Jenner which was widely parodied online.</p>

<p>It gained further traction when conservative pundit Ben Shapiro awkwardly read out the songs lyrics during an episode of his podcast.</p>

<p>WAP was shot in West Hollywood, CA, in the middle of COVID-19 lockdowns.   </p>

<p>Cardi forked out $100k on coronavirus testing to ensure everybody was safe throughout filming.</p>

<p>Show stopper: WAP gained further traction when conservative pundit Ben Shapiro awkwardly read out the songs lyrics during an episode of his podcast. Pictured: The WAP cover, featuring Cardi B (right) and Megan Thee Stallion (left)</p>

<p>The achievement comes as Cardi B, 27, files for divorce from Offset, who is the father to her daughter Kulture Kiari Cephus, 2. </p>

<p>'I didn't wait until he cheated on me again. I didn't wait [for] another controversy with him being involved. I decided to leave,' the singer, whose full name is Belcalis Marlenis Almánzar, told her OnlyFans on September 23.</p>

<p>'If I wanted to stay, I could have stayed. I decided to leave.' </p>

<p>Never a dull moment: The achievement comes as Cardi B (pictured), 27, files for divorce from Offset, who is the father to her daughter Kulture Kiari Cephus, 2</p>
